    "title": "A Simple Day in the City (CHAT)",
    "level": "a1",
    "content": "**Anna:** Hello, Ben.\n**Ben:** Hello, Anna. How are you today?\n**Anna:** I am fine, thank you. And you?\n**Ben:** I am good. I am a little tired.\n**Anna:** Why are you tired?\n**Ben:** I work a lot today. I work in an office.\n**Anna:** Oh, I see. I work in a shop.\n**Ben:** What do you sell in the shop?\n**Anna:** I sell clothes. I sell shirts, pants, and shoes.\n**Ben:** That is nice. Do you like your job?\n**Anna:** Yes, I like my job. I like to talk to people.\n**Ben:** I like to talk to people too.\n\n**Anna:** Where are you now, Ben?\n**Ben:** I am in the city center. I am near a café.\n**Anna:** I like that café. The coffee is good.\n**Ben:** Yes, the coffee is very good. Do you want to sit?\n**Anna:** Yes, I want to sit and talk.\n**Ben:** Okay. Let us sit here.\n\n**Anna:** What do you want to drink?\n**Ben:** I want a coffee with milk.\n**Anna:** I want a tea, please.\n**Ben:** The waiter is coming.\n**Anna:** Hello.\n**Ben:** Hello. Two drinks, please.\n\n**Anna:** Do you live near here?\n**Ben:** Yes, I live near here. I live in a small apartment.\n**Anna:** Do you live alone?\n**Ben:** Yes, I live alone. And you?\n**Anna:** I live with my sister.\n**Ben:** That is nice. How old is your sister?\n**Anna:** She is twenty-five years old.\n**Ben:** My sister is twenty-seven years old.\n\n**Anna:** What do you do after work?\n**Ben:** After work, I go home. I cook dinner.\n**Anna:** Do you like to cook?\n**Ben:** Yes, I like to cook simple food.\n**Anna:** What food do you cook?\n**Ben:** I cook pasta and rice.\n**Anna:** I like pasta. Pasta is good.\n\n**Ben:** Do you like music, Anna?\n**Anna:** Yes, I like music. I like pop music.\n**Ben:** I like pop music too.\n**Anna:** Do you play an instrument?\n**Ben:** No, I do not play an instrument.\n**Anna:** I do not play an instrument either.\n\n**Ben:** What do you do on the weekend?\n**Anna:** On the weekend, I rest. I meet my friends.\n**Ben:** Where do you meet your friends?\n**Anna:** We meet in a park or in a café.\n**Ben:** I like the park. The park is quiet.\n**Anna:** Yes, the park is quiet and green.\n\n**Ben:** Do you like sports?\n**Anna:** Yes, I like sports. I like walking.\n**Ben:** I like walking too.\n**Anna:** Do you walk in the morning or in the evening?\n**Ben:** I walk in the evening.\n**Anna:** I walk in the morning.\n\n**Ben:** Do you have a pet?\n**Anna:** Yes, I have a cat.\n**Ben:** What is your cat’s name?\n**Anna:** Her name is Lily.\n**Ben:** That is a nice name.\n**Anna:** Do you have a pet?\n**Ben:** No, I do not have a pet.\n\n**Anna:** What time do you wake up?\n**Ben:** I wake up at seven in the morning.\n**Anna:** I wake up at six.\n**Ben:** Six is early.\n**Anna:** Yes, it is early, but I like the morning.\n\n**Ben:** Do you like the city?\n**Anna:** Yes, I like the city. There are many shops.\n**Ben:** I like the city too. There are many people.\n**Anna:** Sometimes the city is loud.\n**Ben:** Yes, sometimes it is loud.\n\n**Anna:** What is your favorite place in the city?\n**Ben:** My favorite place is the library.\n**Anna:** I like the library too. I like to read.\n**Ben:** What do you read?\n**Anna:** I read simple books.\n**Ben:** I read newspapers.\n\n**Anna:** Our drinks are here.\n**Ben:** Thank you.\n**Anna:** This tea is good.\n**Ben:** This coffee is very good.\n\n**Anna:** It is nice to talk with you, Ben.\n**Ben:** It is nice to talk with you too, Anna.\n**Anna:** We can meet again.\n**Ben:** Yes, we can meet again tomorrow.\n**Anna:** Tomorrow is good for me.\n**Ben:** Great. See you tomorrow.\n**Anna:** See you tomorrow.",
